    &lt;Title&gt;Money before patient  care&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My GP referred me for a lung function test some 14 months ago and I eventually received an appointment in March 2019.  I saw a very nice consultant who required me to have a lung function and a sleep apnea test.  After the fourteen month wait of seeing the Consultant  I received an appointment for the lung function test which took approximately 10 minutes!  I was told I wouldn’t be having the sleep apnea test because it was not clear who would be paying for it.  I am still waiting for my GP to receive the outcome of this test , I spoke to a lady today 14th April to enquire when I might get the results who informed me I wouldn’t be getting the results, they would go directly to the surgery.  One can only assume,  even though it is my body, that I am too inept to understand  reading a report!   So all in all I am still no better than I was 14 months ago and feeling very let down by the system.

&lt;/CommentText&gt;
